<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-209-045 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 583 752</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer-Aided Engineering  March 1991 v10 n3 p78(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Test drive without leaving home. (University of Iowa's CADCenter's driving simulator)(includes related articles on thecenter and on Cadsi)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mills, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The University of Iowa's Center for Simulation and DesignOptimization is one of the largest organizations in the worlddedicated to simulation-based CAD/CAM research.andP;  One of its newestprojects is the Iowa Driving Simulator, which has a $6 millionCT-6 image generator from Evans andamp; Sutherland.andP;  The CT-6 renders 60frames per second.andP;  The main benefit of the simulator is that anykind of vehicle and operator tests can be conducted withoutputting the operator in danger.andP;  The center is also working onreal-time simulation, dynamics workstations, visualization ofdynamic systems, and new general-purpose multi-body dynamicsimulation code.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SimulationColleges and UniversitiesResearch and DevelopmentImage GenerationCAD/CAMDesignAutomobilesIowa, University of.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>